cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.CYBER

Reasoning: The paper discusses technologies for providing connectivity to rural areas, which falls under the category of networking and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses energy and cost efficiency, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). The discussion of application scenarios and country-specific use cases could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
